Model Structure Analysis Token Analysis Type Subset Analysis

Overview of concepts

name (freq: 11) - Full name | Name
honorific-prefix (freq: 125) - Honorific prefix | Titel
given-name (freq: 491) - Given name | Vorname
additional-name - Additional given name (in Western cultures the middle name)
family-name (freq: 490) - Family name | Nachname
family-name-first - First part of a family name (e.g. the paternal name)
family-name-conjunction - Conjunction between the first and second part of the family name
family-name-second - Second part of a famiily name (e.g. the maternal name)
 
address - Address of a physical location - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML
street-address (freq: 67) - Street address (street and location within the street) | Adresse
address-line1 (freq: 119) - 1st line of street-address
address-line2 (freq: 111) - 2nd line of street-address
address-line3 (freq: 2) - 3rd line of street-address
address-line4 - 4th line of street-address
street-address-alternative-1 - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML; this is a structured representation of a street address
building-location (freq: 15) - Name of a street and identifier for the building | Stra√üe und Hausnummer
street (freq: 315) - Street name | Stra√üe
building (freq: 313) - House number | Hausnummer
address-overflow (freq: 177) - An overflow field for information that is not captured differently in a form | Adresszusatz
locality1 (freq: 517) - City | Stadt/Ort
admin-area1 (freq: 25) - State | Bundesland
postal-code (freq: 513) - Postal code | PLZ
postal-code-prefix - Postal code prefix
postal-code-suffix - Postal code suffix
country (freq: 316) - 2-letter country code (e.g. "DE")
country-name - Name of a country (e.g. "Deutschland") | Land
 
organization (freq: 127) - Name of an organization/company | Organisation/Firma
 
credit-card - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML
cc-name (freq: 190) - Full name of credit card holder
cc-given-name (freq: 10) - Given name of credit card holder
cc-additional-name - Additional name of credit card holder
cc-family-name (freq: 10) - Family name of credit card holder
cc-number (freq: 258) - Credit card number
cc-exp-MMYY (freq: 138) - Credit card expiration date in format MM/YY
cc-exp-MM (freq: 81) - Credit card expiration month (2 digits)
cc-exp-YY (freq: 14) - Credit card expiration date in format YY (2 digits)
cc-exp-MMYYYY (freq: 20) - Credit card expiration date in format MM/YYYY
cc-exp-MM (freq: 81) - Credit card expiration month (2 digits)
cc-exp-YYYY (freq: 73) - Credit card expiration date in format YYYY (4 digits)
cc-csc (freq: 255) - CSC/CVC/CVV number
cc-type (freq: 29) - Credit card type
 
tel (freq: 11) - Full telephone number
tel-country-code (freq: 16) - Country code component of the telephone number
tel-national (freq: 242) - Telephone number without the county code component, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
tel-area-code - Area code component of the telephone number, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
tel-local (freq: 9) - Telephone number without the country code and area code components
tel-local-prefix - First part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
tel-local-suffix - Second part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
tel-extension - Telephone number internal extension code
 
email (freq: 232) - Email address
